<task id="AIPU2-033" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build AuditLogService (append-only compliance log in Cosmos DB)</title>
    <phase>2C</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, cosmos-db, audit, compliance</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-002, AIPU2-006</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Build an AuditLogService that writes an append-only compliance log of all AI interactions
    to a dedicated Cosmos DB container. Each audit entry must record: timestamp, userId,
    sessionId, action performed, tools called, documents accessed, a SHA-256 hash of the
    response content (for tamper detection), safety filter results, and matter context.
    The container must be configured with an immutable policy so that no updates or deletes
    are possible — entries are permanent. Default retention is 7 years to satisfy legal
    compliance requirements. The service must integrate into the existing AI request pipeline
    without affecting streaming latency.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET developer with experience in Cosmos DB immutability policies, compliance logging, and .NET cryptography (SHA-256 hashing).</role>
  <goal>
    Audit entries are written for every AI interaction. Entries are immutable (no update/delete
    possible via SDK). Retention is configured for 7 years. The SHA-256 response hash enables
    tamper detection. The service does not add measurable latency to streaming responses (fire-and-forget write pattern).
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-015-ai-data-governance.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read ADR-015-ai-data-governance.md and ai.md to confirm audit field requirements, retention rules, and immutability constraints before implementing.</step>
    <step>Create AuditLogService.cs in src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Audit/. Define IAuditLogService with LogInteractionAsync(AuditEntry entry) returning ValueTask.</step>
    <step>Define AuditEntry record with all required fields: Timestamp (DateTimeOffset), UserId (string), SessionId (string), TenantId (string), Action (string), ToolsCalled (IReadOnlyList of string), DocumentsAccessed (IReadOnlyList of string), ResponseHash (string, SHA-256 hex), SafetyResults (SafetyCheckResult), MatterContext (MatterRef). Include a computed id property (sessionId + "_" + Guid.NewGuid()) to ensure uniqueness.</step>
    <step>Implement SHA-256 hashing: hash the raw response string using System.Security.Cryptography.SHA256.HashData and encode as lowercase hex. Never store raw response text in the audit log.</step>
    <step>Configure AuditLogService to target the `audit` Cosmos DB container with partition key /tenantId. Use DefaultAzureCredential. Use CreateItemAsync only (never UpsertItemAsync, ReplaceItemAsync, or DeleteItemAsync) to enforce append-only semantics in code.</step>
    <step>Document (in a code comment above the container configuration) that the Cosmos `audit` container must be created with an immutable policy in Bicep/Terraform — reference infrastructure/cosmos/audit-container-policy.json or equivalent. If the file does not exist, create a placeholder JSON file documenting the required policy settings.</step>
    <step>Implement fire-and-forget write: call LogInteractionAsync from the AI pipeline after streaming completes. Wrap in try/catch — audit failures must log at Error level but must not surface to the user or affect the response.</step>
    <step>Register AuditLogService in AddAiPersistenceModule.</step>
    <step>Write unit tests: (a) entry written to Cosmos with correct fields, (b) SHA-256 hash is deterministic for same input, (c) audit failure does not throw, (d) CreateItemAsync used (not Upsert/Replace/Delete).</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>AuditEntry includes all required fields: timestamp, userId, sessionId, action, toolsCalled, documentsAccessed, responseHash (SHA-256), safetyResults, matterContext.</criterion>
    <criterion>Only CreateItemAsync is used — no update or delete operations appear in the service implementation.</criterion>
    <criterion>Response content is hashed (SHA-256), never stored as plaintext in the audit log.</criterion>
    <criterion>Audit write failure does not propagate as an exception to callers or affect streaming.</criterion>
    <criterion>An infrastructure placeholder (policy JSON or Bicep comment) documents the required immutable container policy.</criterion>
    <criterion>Service is registered in AddAiPersistenceModule.</criterion>
    <criterion>All unit tests pass (dotnet test).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
